This paper deals with object affordance understanding, which is a problem commonly addressed in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The approach presented in the paper involves learning features from sensory input, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of a metric learning algorithm and regularization techniques are also common in machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for robot to human communication, which could fall under natural language processing (cs.CL).
